{\rm P}\pars{\Omega_{\vec{r}}}
\Omega_{\vec{r}}\,\,
\xi_{\theta}
\xi_{\phi}
\ds{\half\bracks{-\cos\pars{\theta} + 1} = \xi_{\theta}}
\ds{\pars{~\mbox{or/and}\ \sin\pars{\theta/2} = \root{\xi_{\theta}}~}}
\ds{\phi = 2\pi\,\xi_{\phi}}
\xi_{\theta}
\xi_{\phi}
\left[0, 1\right)
 1 = \int{\rm P}\pars{\Omega_{\vec{r}}}\,\dd\Omega_{\vec{r}} = {\rm P}\pars{\Omega_{\vec{r}}}\int\dd\Omega_{\vec{r}} = {\rm P}\pars{\vec{r}}\pars{4\pi} \quad\imp\quad{\rm P}\pars{\vec{r}} = {1 \over 4\pi} 
 1 = \int_{0}^{\pi}\half\,\sin\pars{\theta}\,\dd\theta\int_{0}^{2\pi} \,{\dd\phi \over 2\pi} 
 \bracks{~\half\,\sin\pars{\theta}\,\dd\theta = \dd\xi_{\theta}\,, \quad\xi_{0} = 0 \imp \theta = 0~}\ \mbox{and}\ \bracks{~{\dd\phi \over 2\pi} = \dd\xi_{\phi}\,,\quad\xi_{0} = 0 \imp \phi = 0~} 
\color{#0000ff}{\large% \theta = 2\arcsin\pars{\root{\xi_{\theta}}}\,,\qquad \phi = 2\pi\xi_{\phi}} 
